
[1]felicity

   FELIC'ITY, n. [L. felicitas, from felix, happy.]

   1. Happiness, or rather great happiness; blessedness; blissfulness;
   appropriately, the joys of heaven.

   2. Prosperity; blessing; enjoyment of good.

   The felicities of her wonderful reign may be complete.

   Females - who confer on life its finest felicities.
